The paper proposes a method using artificial neural networks (ANNs) to estimate unknown compositional input from its output response through an unknown system. This falls under the category of machine learning and specifically, ANNs. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also deals with nonlinear systems, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convex optimization theory for linear systems, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.AI, in that order.
